In [104]:
def plot_co2(df, trendline=True, title='CO '):
    if df.empty:
        return ' '
    
    x = matplotlib.dates.date2num([x.to_pydatetime() for x in df.time])
    y = df.co2
    plt.plot_date(x,y)
    plt.gcf().autofmt_xdate()
    plt.title(title, fontname='NanumSquare')
    
    if trendline:
        # calc the trendline
        z = np.polyfit(x, y, 1)
        p = np.poly1d(z)
        plt.plot(x,p(x),"r--")
        # the line equation:
        print(f"y={z[0]}x+({z[1]})")
    
    plt.show()
    return 0
